I think there is some confusion - one should never load a _labeled video for selecting outliers in the manual GUI, only load original videos. The GUI would display the original video plus outputs. If one selects the “labeled.mp4” that will create issues. 

Not sure this is entirely the issue, but I suspect it is a part as I cannot replicate this issue (Ubuntu 16.04 or 18.04) 

@FancyBrush if it does not fully analyze the video is corrupt and should NOT be used until that is solved!

@MMathisLab 
    Thank you for your advice. I have repaired the original video(the input original video can be normally played) with DivFix++, and use the fixed video as analyze_video() input. However, analyze_video() still can not fully finished(64%). How can I make sure that the corrupt issue is solved? Do you have any recommended tools for .avi corrupt reapir? 
    Same with AdoNunes's issue, **the input video is indeed the original video.** During refining the labels, as index moving forward, the labels seemed to belong to the frame that comes next a few.
